Sandy notes**  
  
**1. Overall objective of the process**  
	•	Core task:  
	•	Compare **FO internal price vs external market price**  
	•	For each futures contract:  
  
Difference = Internal\ Price - External\ Price  
  
PnL\ Impact = Difference \times Position  
  
👉 Purpose:  
	•	Check if **trader marking is accurate**  
	•	Quantify **valuation impact (PV / PnL)**  
  
⸻  
  
**2. Tool used: Futures Checker (central system)**  
	•	This tool:  
	•	Pulls **all required data automatically**  
	•	Data includes:  
	•	Positions  
	•	Internal prices (RAMP)  
	•	External reference prices  
	•	Static data  
  
👉 This is the **execution layer** of MAP  
  
⸻  
  
**3. How you start daily process**  
  
Steps:  
	1.	Go to **User Settings**  
	2.	Select:  
	•	Region  
	•	Business date  
	3.	Open:  
	•	**Futures Map Review**  
  
👉 System then loads full dataset  
  
⸻  
  
**4. Data sources (very important mapping)**  
  
**A. Static data**  
	•	Futures code, tenor, etc.  
	•	Source:  
	•	Internal static system (Sierra)  
	•	Ultimately sourced from Bloomberg  
  
⸻  
  
**B. Position data**  
	•	Source:  
	•	Booking system (**stock**)  
	•	Aggregation:  
	•	Portfolio level  
  
⸻  
  
**C. Internal price (BNP price)**  
	•	Source:  
	•	**RAMP system**  
	•	This is:  
	•	FO contributed price  
  
⸻  
  
**D. External price**  
	•	Source:  
	•	From earlier flow:  
	•	Reference Close Asia  
	•	Ramp / mid / exchange logic  
  
👉 This is what you validate against  
  
⸻  
  
**5. PnL impact calculation columns**  
	•	Original PnL:  
	•	In contract currency (USD, GBP etc.)  
	•	Converted PnL:  
	•	EUR equivalent  
  
👉 Used for:  
	•	Risk / materiality assessment  
  
⸻  
  
**6. Review / override fields**  
  
Columns:  
	•	Review Price  
	•	VRC Comment  
	•	Review Basis  
  
👉 Used when:  
	•	Price issue identified  
	•	Manual override required  
  
👉 Connects to:  
	•	Upload process (earlier screenshot)  
  
⸻  
  
**7. Revaluation Set (CRITICAL CONCEPT)**  
  
This defines:  
  
👉 **Timing of pricing**  
  
Examples:  
	•	Asia Close  
	•	Tokyo Close  
	•	London Close  
	•	Official  
  
⸻  
  
**Meaning**  
	•	Each portfolio is assigned a **valuation timing**  
	•	Determines:  
	•	Which snapshot (from earlier “Future Snap” files) is used  
  
⸻  
  
**Regional mapping**  
	•	Asia / Tokyo → APAC  
	•	London → EMEA  
	•	Official → US  
  
👉 Directly ties to:  
	•	Your **multiple timestamp snapshots earlier**  
  
⸻  
  
**8. Organizational mapping**  
  
Columns show:  
	•	Middle office responsible  
	•	Desk (GPL / FBL)  
  
⸻  
  
**Definitions**  
	•	GPL = Global Product Line  
	•	FBL = Desk classification  
  
👉 Used for:  
	•	Ownership  
	•	Escalation  
  
⸻  
  
**KEY FLOW (CONNECTED TO ALL PREVIOUS CONTEXT)**  
	1.	**Snapshots (Future Snap files)** →  
	2.	**Uploaded to RAMP (Reference Close Asia)** →  
	3.	**Mapping decides price source + timing** →  
	4.	**Futures Checker loads data** →  
	5.	**Internal vs External comparison** →  
	6.	**PnL impact calculated**  
  